Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "gad" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations:

1. *Gadno* je napolju, pada kiša. (*Nasty* weather outside, it's raining.)
2. Ti si pravi *gad*, ne mogu da verujem da si to uradio. (You are a real *jerk*, I can't believe you did that.)
3. Ne znam kako si mogao da pojedeš to *gadljivo* jelo. (I don't know how you could eat that *disgusting* dish.)
4. Ta osoba je stvarno *gadna*, ne želim da se družim s njom. (That person is really *nasty*, I don't want to hang out with them.)
5. Molim te, skloni ovo *gadje* smeće s poda. (Please, remove this *filthy* garbage from the floor.)
6. Ona me je pogledala sa *gadjenjem* kada sam joj rekao istinu. (She looked at me with *disgust* when I told her the truth.)
7. *Gadovi* su mi pojeli sav usev u bašti. (*Pests* have eaten all my crops in the garden.)
8. Zbog njenog *gadnog* ponašanja, izgubila je mnoge prijatelje. (Because of her *bad* behavior, she lost many friends.)
9. U ovom *gadnom* gradu ne bih želeo da živim ni dana. (I wouldn't want to live even a day in this *awful* city.)

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any further questions.